<node id="AuthorizationQuantity">
  <data key="d0">AuthorizationQuantity</data>
  <data key="d1">authorizationquantity</data>
  <data key="d2">AuthorizationQuantity refers to the authorized amount of data usage within various systems, encompassing several key metrics including purchase quantity, average usage, utilization rate, and peak usage details. It is a critical metric that helps in managing and optimizing data usage by providing insights into current usage patterns and suggesting necessary expansions to meet future demands.

The term AuthorizationQuantity is used in different contexts with varying specifics. In one context, it pertains to the Splunk system, where the current average usage is 133.26GB, with a suggested expansion to 20GB. Another instance involves an authorized amount of data usage with a current average usage of 1398GB and a recommended expansion to 375 GB. Additionally, AuthorizationQuantity can refer to scenarios where the suggested expansion is from 100GB to 132GB or from 150 GB to an average of 661.01 GB. In another instance, it involves a recommended expansion from 375 GB to 1276 GB.

In other contexts, AuthorizationQuantity refers to the authorized usage limit with specific details such as a current total of 285GB and an average usage of 239.38GB. Another description mentions an authorization quantity of 150 GB with an average usage of 630 GB, suggesting an expansion. The term also includes details such as the recommended expansion, current authorization volume, and average usage.

Specific instances of AuthorizationQuantity include a suggested expansion from 100GB to 124GB and another instance where the authorized usage limit for the Splunk system has a current average usage of 55.15GB with a recommended expansion to 20GB. Additionally, there is an authorization quantity that includes a total authorization of 131 GB and an average usage of 117.92 GB.

Overall, AuthorizationQuantity is a versatile metric used across different systems to manage data usage effectively, ensuring that authorized limits are adhered to while providing actionable insights for future expansions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-203eba714089c79438cfc39755f054ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56b76e765b58a558604d5d6f2575d2ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67cc5a5ed7a1cbea5f9e6d5f5d08ab51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-726c374f489423e007bce76f7810b46e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-886b4b629f3088ef8656c792cf7b3e8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f1e5469f6278ea8a34bff96b293b69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41be59e9bae9e87a716afd8b5a9e9ee1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-490df5a6810de4f040c4fe2681e6ed6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2a0171ee9d19cc664d4d041d3e73ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc4bf66788ce00c23c3e736753ea50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04465635a6b88183cbabbfe7e25635dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4861ed7c0c566a81f361adb6811a1523&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9648988cb67db9843bc13754ac3d6ab6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dddcb833d814b293bd936732652206d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a81645d1d338ac013fa594b14c35640</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
