<node id="VersionUpdate">
  <data key="d0">VersionUpdate</data>
  <data key="d1">versionupdate</data>
  <data key="d2">VersionUpdate is a process or set of recommendations related to updating software versions, primarily focusing on Splunk systems and associated components like Universal Forwarders (UF). The primary goal of VersionUpdate is to address vulnerabilities and ensure system security.

The descriptions provided highlight several key points regarding VersionUpdate. One common theme is the need to update from various older versions to a more recent version. For instance, there are recommendations to upgrade from version 9.3.3/2025.02.26 to the latest version 10.0.2/2025.11.14 due to vulnerabilities in the current versions. This is particularly relevant for E客戶's Splunk instance, which also faces similar vulnerabilities. Additionally, there are recommendations to upgrade from version 9.3.8/2025.11.14 to the latest version 10.0.2/2025.11.14.

However, there are instances where VersionUpdate involves evaluating the current version against the latest one and deciding not to upgrade. For example, when the current version is 9.3.6/2025.07.31 or 9.3.8, it was decided not to upgrade to version 10.0.2 due to the absence of major vulnerabilities or bugs in the current versions.

Another aspect of VersionUpdate involves updating the Splunk system from an older version, such as 8.0.6, to a more recent version like 10.0.1 or 10.0.2. This process includes recommendations to expand authorization usage before proceeding with the update.

It is also noted that the current version of Splunk and UF is 9.3.8/2025.11.14, with an end-of-service date of 2026.06.24. This information is crucial for planning future updates and ensuring that systems remain supported.

In summary, VersionUpdate is a critical process aimed at enhancing system security by addressing vulnerabilities through software updates. The decision to upgrade depends on the presence of vulnerabilities in the current version and the availability of a more secure latest version.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-203eba714089c79438cfc39755f054ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56b76e765b58a558604d5d6f2575d2ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67cc5a5ed7a1cbea5f9e6d5f5d08ab51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-726c374f489423e007bce76f7810b46e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-886b4b629f3088ef8656c792cf7b3e8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f1e5469f6278ea8a34bff96b293b69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41be59e9bae9e87a716afd8b5a9e9ee1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-490df5a6810de4f040c4fe2681e6ed6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2a0171ee9d19cc664d4d041d3e73ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc4bf66788ce00c23c3e736753ea50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04465635a6b88183cbabbfe7e25635dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4861ed7c0c566a81f361adb6811a1523&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9648988cb67db9843bc13754ac3d6ab6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76068a2f95fd89e7ceb4741d4eb478ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dddcb833d814b293bd936732652206d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a81645d1d338ac013fa594b14c35640</data>
