<edge source="World Athletics Federation" target="Noah Carter">
  <data key="d7">79.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Noah Carter and the World Athletics Federation are connected through a significant athletic achievement. The World Athletics Federation has officially recognized and validated Noah Carter's new world record in the 100-meter (100m) sprint, which he achieved during a championship event. This validation by the governing body of athletics confirms Carter's performance as an official world record in the sport.

The validation process underscores the importance of Carter's accomplishment within the athletic community. The World Athletics Federation's endorsement serves to authenticate his new 100m sprint record, solidifying its status as a legitimate and officially recognized achievement. This recognition highlights both Noah Carter's exceptional performance and the rigorous standards upheld by the World Athletics Federation in validating such records.

The World Athletics Federation oversees and validates Noah Carter's new 100m sprint record, ensuring that his accomplishment meets the highest standards of athletic excellence. The validation process involves a thorough review and confirmation of Carter's performance, reinforcing the credibility of his world record. This endorsement by the World Athletics Federation is crucial in establishing Carter's achievement as an official milestone in the sport.

The consistent validation by the World Athletics Federation emphasizes the significance of Noah Carter's 100m sprint record, which was set during a championship event. The federation's role in overseeing and validating this record underscores its commitment to maintaining the integrity and excellence of athletic records worldwide.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees and validates Noah Carter's new 100m sprint record.</data>
